      <hedline>
        <hl1>Santa's Quarters Looted</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">AP</byline>
      <dateline>JACKSONVILLE, Fla., Dec. 3</dateline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>LEAD: The offices and a warehouse of a man who has been Santa Claus for many underpriviledged children were looted of about $500 in merchandise Wednesday. ''I think anybody would have to be pretty bad off to steal from the poor,'' said Dorcas Drake, whose annual toy drive serves 50,000 children. Mr. Drake, a retired justice of the peace, has served as Santa Claus for 30 years.</p>
      </block>
